Toubou come from Garamantes, not the other way around. The Garamantes were an ancient population group, they cannot come from any modern ethnic groups, that's why 'pastoralists from the Sahara' and 'Berber tribes' already account for the diversity of any human populations both south and north of the continent. Tuareg and Toubou pages also mention this already on their ethnogenesis: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuareg_people, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toubou_people#History
